<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id602cc25a-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58" identifier="/us/usc/t30/s1012"><num value="1012">§ 1012.</num><heading> Waiver, suspension, or reduction of rental or royalty</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may waive, suspend, or reduce the rental or royalty for any lease or portion thereof in the interests of conservation and to encourage the greatest ultimate recovery of geothermal resources, if he determines that this is necessary to promote development or that the lease cannot be successfully operated under the lease terms.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id602cc25b-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/581/s13">Pub. L. 91–581, § 13</ref>, <date date="1970-12-24">Dec. 24, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1570">84 Stat. 1570</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tII/s236/13">Pub. L. 109–58, title II, § 236(13)</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/672">119 Stat. 672</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
